While millions of families are squashed into cramped city flats with no outdoor space, the majority are dreaming of living somewhere else, according to a poll published today.

In an ideal world, they would like to live in a detached Victorian house in the South West of England, such as Devon or Cornwall, with a large garden, a garage and a walk-in wardrobe.

Around 3,500 homeowners were asked, if money was no object, where they would like to live and the sort of home they would like to own.

Despite having an unlimited budget, most people said they would like only four to five bedrooms although they would theoretically have enough money to buy a castle or a mansion.

